Red Sea main basin: Egypt (
Klunzinger 1870, as
Chrysophrys berda
), Sudan ( Iwatsuki & Carpenter 2009 ), Eritrea ( Pellegrin 1912 , as Chrysophuys datnia ; Tortonese 1935, as
Sparus berda
), Saudi Arabia (Rüppell 1838, as
Chrysophrys berda
), Yemen (Forsskål in Niebuhr 1775 , as
Sparus berda
; see Fricke 2008 ).

Remark: A single specimen was recorded from the Mediterranean (
Ben Souissi et al . 2014
).
